3e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ccite\u003eScreenshot: The Verge\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eMosseri also said that Threads is adding a way to “markup” a post you’re resharing. Based on early versions of the feature \u003ca href=\"https://www.threads.net/@lindseygamble_/post/DE8ykFjMCx4\"\u003eshared by users\u003c/a\u003e, it looks like it will let you draw over, highlight, or add arrows to an existing post. This feature is rolling out to a “few countries with more to come soon.”\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eThere are some big changes in store for Threads, which will \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2025/1/13/24342930/meta-threads-community-notes-leaks\"\u003ealso trade fact-checking for Community Notes\u003c/a\u003e as part of Meta’s broader moderation shift. The X competitor will start \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2025/1/8/24339385/instagram-threads-politics-moderation-adam-mosseri\"\u003eadding political content\u003c/a\u003e to recommendations as well.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eMost Popular\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eMost Popular\u003c/p\u003e\u003col\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2025/1/22/24349499/nfl-patriots-bluesky-accounts-not-allowed-x-meta-threads\"\u003e\u003ch2\u003eNFL teams can’t use Bluesky\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003chr/\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2025/1/22/24349416/google-gemini-virtual-assistant-samsung-siri-alexa\"\u003e\u003ch2\u003eGoogle’s Gemini is already winning the next-gen assistant wars\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003chr/\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2025/1/23/24340743/star-trek-section-31-review-paramount-plus\"\u003e\u003ch2\u003eStar Trek: Section 31 is firing on all cylinders\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003chr/\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\